          <title locale="en">Freedom and Responsibility in Existential Counselling</title>
          <abstract locale="en">&lt;p&gt;This article explores the interplay between freedom and responsibility in existential counselling. Through case studies and philosophical analysis, we argue that genuine therapeutic change requires confronting both the possibilities and the burdens of human freedom.&lt;/p&gt;</abstract>
          <copyrightHolder locale="en">Maria Smith</copyrightHolder>
          <copyrightYear>2024</copyrightYear>
